# .cursorrules
You are an expert developer in Electron, React, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.

Project layout:
- Main process: src/main/ (CommonJS, Node types)
- Preload: src/preload/
- Renderer (React): src/renderer/src/
- Shared types: src/types/

Conventions:
- Use functional React components with Hooks only.
- Style with Tailwind utility classes; avoid global CSS outside base/components/utilities.
- Cross-platform (Windows/Mac). Avoid OS-specific shell calls in renderer.
- Never access Node APIs from renderer — use preload contextBridge.
- IPC channel names live in src/types/ipc.ts as const.
- Secrets: .env read by main process, forwarded via IPC.
